review_blob: Poured golden, slightly hazy, with a thick pretty permanent head that left thick sticky rings of lacing.  Smelled sweet. Tasted even sweeter.  No hops. Left a sticky, musty taste in my mouth.  Worth trying, not worth trying again.

12 oz bottle, bottled 12/13/06, poured 2/17/07. Served at about 55 degrees. Poured a light, copper brown with a medium tan head that was gone shortly after the pour. Smells piney, slightly floral, with a sweet malty backbone. Has a thick, creamy mouthfeel, with good, unyeilding carbonation. Tastes of hops, very bitter, good strong malt character. Alcohol is hidden pretty well, but still detectable. Hops linger on the tongue for a few minutes before fading. Very very tasty

2007, aged 1 month.  Poured into a Chimay trappist glass. Pours a deep red mahogany with a thick (~1") creamy head. Head slowly disappears, leaving good lacing behind and after every sip.  Smells like a super hopped IPA. Tastes like a super hopped IPA, with the barleywine sweetness sneaking in towards the end.  Poured with a slight chill (about 50 degrees), but flavors started opening up the warmer it got. For a barley wine, it was incredibly drinkable.  Cant wait to see what the rest of the 6 pack taste like down the road.

12(ish) ounce bottle, poured into a trappist (Chimay) glass.  Pours a very dark brown, almost opaque.  Has a very thin head that dissapears almost immediately.  Smells malty, citrusy, smokey with a hoppy background.  Very little hop in the taste, more fruity malt, very much like a brown ale.  Palate is kind of disappointing. The carbonation it has is extremely tiny bubbles, feels almost flat.  Not a bad beer, but not worth the price tag ($3.99/bottle)

This is a very good beer. Nice balanced. Pours a deep brown with a nice white head that leaves beautiful lacing around the glass. Smells sweet, spicy, malty.  Tastes delicious, very well balanced, tiny bubbles make my tongue happy. Has a nice hop bite at the end. Underrated on this site.  Probably my favorite session beer out.

Wow... A-B really actually took time to come up with this one. Pours a cloudy brown, with red hints. Has a good thick white head and a ring around the outside of the glass maintains through every pull on the beer. Lacks any lacing, which is dissapointing. Has a sweet, malty scent.  Nice fruit flavor, with slight hop bite and something else in the ending. Could be Sorghum. I am incredibly impressed. Much better than that Red Hook crap A-B tries to sell as real beer.


As I scan through other ratings I feel many people see the A-B crest on the label and automatically feel they CANNOT rate it above a 2.5. Perhaps I am rating it high, as it is made by A-B, and it is drinkable...
UPDATED: FEB 15, 2007

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: poured like a normal wheat beer.  No real head. no lacing. tasted like fruity pebbles.  nothing i will try again

pours a deep red/brown with a good head.  Has a strong, sweet aroma with definite alcohol undertones.  Sweet, fruity flavors with a good alcohol bite.  Has a good palate with lots of tiny bubbles.  good barley wine.

Pours a dark deep slightly transparent brown with small off white head.  Smells of rich toffee, hazelnut, and almost caramel immediately jump from this beer.  Has strong nutty/chocolate/caramel flavors with a rich malt finish. Not much in the way of hoppiness, which is typical of a nut brown.  Its a little too sweet and sugary in the palate, feeling like they added molasses at the end.  Good beer, nonetheless

Pours a nice brown-gold with a decent head which disappears quickly.  Has a citrusy, hoppy scent.  Has a thick, rich mouthfeel with small carbonation.  Nice malty, flavor underwritten by a hoppy bite.  Good flavor, good pale ale, but not the best
UPDATED: FEB 15, 2007

Pours a red, coppery brown with a medium head that leaves a pretty constant thin head.  Has almost no scent, kind of disappointing.  Slightly bitter, fairly malty.  Nice mouthfeel, thick with light carbonation. Not a typical ESB, not a bad brew, very tasty.  Good, but there are better brews from Stoudts

Pours a deep dark brown with little head.  Has a very sweet malty smell. Sweet, nutty, almost too sweet.  Very thin in the mouth, like carbonated water.  Not the best ESB Ive had, but not the worst beer.  Probably wouldnt buy it again

Pours a copper brown with practically no head which completely disappears quickly.  Has a sweet taste with a hit of hops.  Finishes like a belgian wheat ale.  Not bad, has a good alcohol bite to it.  Good enough beer, but way overpriced ($12/4-pack)
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Pours dark dark brown with a thick tan head that disappears into a thin top.  smells hoppy and slightly sweet.  Tastes slightly sweet with a good hoppy bite and a sort of smoky flavor.  Kind of thin in the mouth, small carbonation keeps it interesting.  Overall, a good brown ale.  But nothing too spectacular
beer_name: Shipyard Brewers Choice Special Ale Brown Ale (05-06, 09-13)

review_blob: Poured black as night with a thick beige/tan head that slowly disappeared.  Left a thin head that remained the entire course or the beer.  Smelled of toffee, coffee, and chocolate.  Tastes match the smells, with a bitterness rounding it out.  Nice creamy feel with fine carbonation.  Good stout, not too sweet, not too chocolatey

I am very unimpressed with the Tommyknocker brews.  Pours a light copper brown with a light head that never completely leaves the beer.  Leaves pretty good lacing.  Smells very piney.  Tastes slightly piney, slightly bitter, but nothing too impressive.  All in all a marginal beer, but probably the best Tommyknocker beer Ive had yet.

Wow, Tommyknocker seems to believe in order to make beer, you have to add more sugar than hops.  It tasted way too sweet from start to finish.  Had no bitterness.  Smelled very mapley.  Had very fine carbonation.  Thick creamy mouthfeel, which was good. Poured dark brown, almost opaque, which was good.  But the important part, taste, fell way short.

Pours light yellow with a small head that disappeared immediately.  Smells about like any other Lager.  Grassy smell.  Tastes weak, very watery.  Leaves very little aftertaste.  No bitterness, no hoppiness, slight malty flavor.  Another mediocre beer by Tommyknocker

Batch 4. Very tasty.  Pours a rich orange/amber with a thick head that sticks around for a while.  leaves thin lacing, and only if left for a minute.  Two quick sips leaves none.  Has a distinct piney scent.  Tastes very dry, very hoppy, matching the scent.  Very good finish, leavin no lingering unpleasant tastes.  Another great Imp IPA
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: A little too sweet for me. Poured a very dark brown, almost black.  Very sweet, too sweet.  another lager I can cross off my list

A wonderful Double IPA.  Poured a deep reddish/brown with a good off white head that left nice lacing.  Very hoppy, very bitter, very good.  Smelled of citrus hops with floral attributes.  Had a good malty sweetness that rounded out the flavor.

Not sure what all the hype is about with this beer.  A good beer, but I wouldnt go and call it the best beer in the world.  Had a yeasty, hoppy flavor.  Good beer, I wouldnt turn it down, but I doubt Ill buy it again.
Very refreshing. Like water. But with less flavor.  Pours very pale with a thick white head.  Smells slightly citrusy.  Not a good beer to start my Tommyknocker experience with.

22 oz. bottled.  Poured a light tan color with a thick high head that slowly disappeared and left good lacing.  Kind of light on the scent, a slightly sweet scent if you stick your nose right in there.  Kind of light on the flavor, too.  Not as hoppy as I like my IPAs.  But, it is refreshing and is still quite enjoyable.

Im pretty sure this is the same beer, the one I sampled was 9.5% alcohol.  Anyway, it poured a golden orange tan color, with a thick low tan head that disappeared quickly but left great lacing.  smelled yeasty, slightly citrusy, slightly flowery.  Very enticing.  Had a wonderful mouthfeel, good small carbonation that seemed to be present all the way down.  Tasted mellow at first, but finished very hoppy, nice bitterness, with a slight alcohol bite at the very end.  Should be rated higher in my opinion
beer_name: Rogue XS Imperial India Pale Ale (IPA)

review_blob: I wasnt too impressed. Came in a ceramic bottle.  The long skinny neck caused problems with smooth pouring, possibly resulting in a slightly more flat beer than it is intended to be: very little carbonation with extremely small bubbles.  Not a flavor I appreciated either.  Too unremarkable, barely any hoppiness, all too sweet for me.

The first thing about this beer is the strong fruit smell, which is not appealing to me.  It hits you before you even pour.  It pours a deep dark brown with a thick sudsy tan head, that for me took forever to disappear.  But the flavor was great.  Tasted slightly sweet, with some subtle fruit undertones.  Had a marginally bitter end.  Couldnt pick out any alcohol flavor, which was noted in some other peoples comments.  Very good beer, even lacking the bitter hops

Pours a deep brown with a  small offwhite head.  Leaves good lacing.  Smells citrusy.  Has a smooth taste that finishes with a good bite from the hops.  Good bitter brew, enjoyed with a good greasy burger.  Worth checking out again
A good pale ale, but I need something stronger, something with more bite, more hops.  Lacks a memorable finish

Ok beer, not bad for the price tag, I can get a case for about $20.  Leaves a lingering metallic taste that has stuck with me since I finished the beer an hour ago.  Better than most mainstream beers.
Just a generally unremarkable beer.  Pretty unacceptable on all acounts. Has a slight hoppy finish, but there are many better brews
Pours a hazy golden with a white head that leaves no lacing.  Smells hoppy, slightly acidic.  Tastes mildly bitter, not as much as an IPA.  Good beer all in all, but not one of the "Greats"

2005. Pours a deep red brown with a small off white head that disappears quickly,  little to no lacing remaining.  Smells sweet.  Tastes slightly hoppy, with definite alcohol present.  Not a regular in my book, but no barleywine is...
Good IPA.  Good flavor, good smell, good appearance.  Doesnt stand out though.  Worth buying again, but Im going for my other preferred IPAs
beer_name: Lost Coast Indica India Pale Ale

review_blob:
Good beer, but misleading with the name.  Id be interested to see what the IBU is for this, but it sure isnt brutal.  It is, however, a very good beer.  Smooth, with a nice bite.  Good smell, nice feel to the mouth.  Pours a cloudy orange red.
Definitely something I could get used to drinking
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Very smooth nice taste.  Good deep brown color.  Very considerable lack of smell.  Good blend of hops malt.  Tastes good, feels good.  Dogfish Head strikes again

Pours a rich deep mahogany red with a brown head that disappears completely quickly.  Smells sickingly sweet.  Tastes as sweet as it smells.  Reminds me of the old cough syrup before technology improved it. Not much hop flavor, no bitter aftertaste.  Has a very nice creamy feel to it.  Not worth the price
beer_name: Avery The Beast Grand Cru Ale

review_blob: Pours a dark brown with reddish coloring.  Has a nice thick brown head that attenuates nicely.  Smells of chocolate and hops.  Creamy, thick, appealing feel in the mouth.  Tastes hoppy with chocolate undertones.  More of a stout than a brown ale.  Not my type of beer, but good for the style

Pours black, no light makes it through the pint glass.  Has a high ruddy brown head that disappears quickly but leaves good lacing.  Slightly sweet scent, but not all that impressive.  Heavy on the coffee and chicory, very light on the hops.  I was not too impressed, DFH should put this one away with their raison beer

Brown/orange color to it with a white light head that outlasts the beer.  Good lacing.  Weak aroma, lacking there, but the little bit it has is very appealing.  Very hoppy taste with bitter undertones, but nowhere near overwhelming.  Leaves a lingering bitter flavor.  Overall, very good IPA
I do not know what possessed Dogfish Head to destroy their reputation with making a raison beer.  Way too sweet, way too fruity.  An unfortunate addition to DFHs selection

One of the best IPAs Ive ever had.  Dogfish head gets another beer right.  Dark ruddy brown color and decent head and lacing.  Aroma is very appealing.  Great hoppy flavor, but no where near overwhelming.  An almost perfect IPA

Very bland, has no initial flavor, head is small and disappears quickly.  Nice brown amber color.  Sweet smell to it.  Leaves a slightly unpleasant aftertaste after most of the beer is gone.  Not something Id be willing to spend the amount they are charging for it.

Tastes like a high quality cheap american beer with a speciality beer price tag

i only give it .1 above absolute crap because it is marginally better than Budweiser (absolute crap).  Mostly because it doesnt leave as much of a cheap taste in your mouth after you finished the stuff
horrible. tastes like a drunk hobos urine. only good for college kids drinking games
Rock Art perfected the Barley Wine.  Wonderful flavor, great appearance.  Smooth, slightly sweet, with a lingering appealing aftertaste.  One of my favorites
Simply put, it tastes like medicine.  A very disappointing selection from Sam Adams
Good smooth flavor, Nice hazy look, Great with a lemon, good without.  A good mild Hefeweizen, not for those who enjoy a stronger more wheaty Hefeweizen
